<h2>Delaware Incentives & Rebates</h2>
<p>Delaware offers a comprehensive array of incentives that make solar panel and HVAC investments highly attractive financially. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit for solar installations through 2032, applying to the total system cost including equipment, installation, and permitting. This credit can be carried forward if it exceeds the homeowner's tax liability in the installation year, ensuring full value realization over time.</p>

<p>The state's Green Energy Program provides grants and low-interest financing for renewable energy systems, including both solar panels and high-efficiency HVAC systems. Delaware's Sustainable Energy Utility (SEU), operated by Energize Delaware, offers rebates up to \$4,500 for ENERGY STAR certified heat pump installations and additional incentives for comprehensive home energy improvements. The program also provides free energy audits to help homeowners identify the most cost-effective efficiency upgrades.</p>

<p>Delmarva Power offers several programs that benefit both solar and HVAC customers. Their net metering program provides full retail rate credits for excess solar production, while their Peak Energy Savings Credit provides bill credits for customers who reduce electricity usage during peak demand periods. The utility also offers rebates for ENERGY STAR appliances and HVAC systems, with additional incentives available for smart thermostat installations that can optimize energy usage in conjunction with solar production.</p>

<p>Local municipalities in Delaware may offer additional property tax exemptions or abatements for renewable energy installations. Many Delaware cities and counties exempt the added value of solar installations from property tax assessments, allowing homeowners to benefit from increased property values without higher tax bills. Some areas also offer expedited permitting processes for solar installations, reducing installation timelines and soft costs.</p>

